  Published, Sat, 8 Feb 1997 17:18:45 +0000

======================================================================

Judgement: TRUE

Reasons and arguments:

While Justices are not specifically mentioned in Rule 217, Rule 1564
does require them to consider the correctness of Judgements which
would seem to require them to at least take 217 into account.
Further, Rule 1564 allows the determination of the Justices to become
Judgements which MUST be in accord with the portion of Rule 217 which
precedes the semicolon.

While this alone would seem to indicate that the Statement is TRUE, it
could be argued that it does not CLEARLY indicate Justices are to be
so bound.  Therefore, (ironically) under direction of Rule 217, I have
considered game custom, commonsense, past Judgements, and the best
interests of the game, and, in my opinion, each leads me to also
consider the Statement TRUE.  Therefore, have I so Judged.

